At 19:17 26/06/00 IRST, you wrote:
>How could I display my graphic files together with pretrial fixation
>point display and post-trial masking?

You need to put each visual event in a separate frame, with / marks
separating each frame.

For example:

+1 <ms %500> "+" / * <ms %500> <bmp> "target" / <ms% 2000> <bmp> "mask" /;

will display the fixation cross (+ sign) for approx 500ms, then the target
for approx 500ms and then the mask for 2000ms. RT will be measured from the
onset of the target item (as indicated by the *).

Matt


